values.description:
Models with semi-transparent textures currently generates incorrect shadows (just rectangular blocks). This PR adds new shadow caster shaders that works with textures that have alpha channels. 

Here the shaders are added to this model as an example but eventually we'll will need to find a generic way to do it from within Gazebo in order not to duplicate these shaders in different models.

![tree_shadows.jpg](data/bitbucket.org/repo/EgGzpd/images/1210495868-tree_shadows.jpg)

values.description:
The `hinged_door` model has a `10 N-m` friction (more accurately, stiction) parameter in its handle joint. This effectively means that someone would need to push down with approximately 20 lbs of force on the center of this door handle before the handle even *begins* to rotate.

This is problematic for robots whose fingers may not be able to apply that much force. It's also not a very realistic parameter for a door handle.

This PR removes the stiction parameter and introduces a spring coefficient. Most door handles have a light spring and relatively little stiction (if they're well maintained), so these parameters should be more reflective of a real life scenario.

If we should do any kind of versioning on the model, please let me know.
values.title: Replace friction of hinged_door with a spring

values.title: Add parameterized trisphere_cycle model to be used for testing wheel slip

values.description:
I made a tricycle model with spherical wheels and front steering. It will be used in a test for the gazebo WheelSlipPlugin (added in [gazebo PR 2950](https://bitbucket.org/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/2950/adding-wheelslipplugin-for-adding-wheel/diff)).

![trike.png](data/bitbucket.org/repo/EgGzpd/images/3164252219-trike.png)

The model has an embedded-ruby template, and I've tinkered with a "chopper" model using the following patch:

~~~
diff -r 97a7daf87cb5 trisphere_cycle/model.sdf.erb
--- a/trisphere_cycle/model.sdf.erb    Thu May 31 13:29:34 2018 -0700
+++ b/trisphere_cycle/model.sdf.erb    Thu May 31 16:30:41 2018 -0700
@@ -7,11 +7,11 @@
 
   # Geometry
   wheel_radius    = 0.15
-  wheelbase       = 6 * wheel_radius
-  half_track      = wheelbase * Math.tan(30 * Math::PI/180)
-  caster_angle    = 10 * Math::PI / 180.0
+  wheelbase       = 10 * wheel_radius
+  half_track      = 0.8*wheelbase * Math.tan(30 * Math::PI/180)
+  caster_angle    = 50 * Math::PI / 180.0
   fork_length     = 1.5 * wheel_radius * Math.sqrt(2)
-  headtube_length = 0.5 * fork_length
+  headtube_length = 1.0 * fork_length
   front_steer_L   = headtube_length + fork_length
   front_steer_dx  = front_steer_L * Math.sin(caster_angle)
   front_steer_dz  = front_steer_L * Math.cos(caster_angle)
@@ -29,7 +29,7 @@
   fork_offset = fork_length - 0.5*front_steer_L
   wheel_x0     = rear_steer_dx
   wheel_y0     = half_track
-  steer_limit  = 55 * Math::PI / 180.0
+  steer_limit  = 30 * Math::PI / 180.0
 
   rear_wheel_locations = {
     "rear_left"   => {:x0 => -wheel_x0, :y0 => wheel_y0 },
~~~

The chopper is not committed in this branch; it's just an example of how the parameterized template can be used.

![chopper.png](data/bitbucket.org/repo/EgGzpd/images/1384378253-chopper.png)

* updated CMakeList to use CMAKE\_INSTALL\_PREFIX correctly. style update to make install lines easier to read.

this also allows the `make package` command to create non-empty distributable files \([https://public.kitware.com/pipermail/cmake/2010-February/035169.html](https://public.kitware.com/pipermail/cmake/2010-February/035169.html)\)
